rComments: he's a nice man but SO boring. classes are painful to follow because he talks so much and yet says so little. a lot of reading to do. honestly I would not recommend him, his classes are not stimulating

Really nice person. He does care a lot for his student and listen to them. he really likes group projects. What I dislike about him is the fact that his lecture are based on the reading, it is literally a summary of the reading he makes us do before the class, so a bit useless to go to the lecture when you have a good understanding of the reading.

J'ai eu ce prof deux fois de suite et à ses deux classes j'ai eu A+. Il est vraiment gentil et super accessible en dehors des périodes de cours. C'est un prof qui connait beaucoup sa matière et on apprend des choses vraiment intéressantes dans son cours. Il a la réussite de ses élèves à cœur et cela se voit.

Great prof! He is approachable, fair, and accommodating. His classes are super interesting and easy to follow. He uses the same format for every class: summary of previous class, outline for class, concepts/ definition, explanation, and example. He often uses videos and class participation to convey material and engage students.

This teacher is not there to make you fail. there's an extra 10 % for attendance. the class before an exam he gives you questions to study with the answers and the same questions are in the exam. no final exam, just a group project with an oral. really easy.

He was a really kind professor but was not the best at explaining theories. He was not clear on what he wanted for final paper or exams but he was easy on grades. He take sooo much time to put grades out though!
C'est un excellent professeur. Il a réellement la réussite de ses étudiants à coeur. Il fait des révisions avant les examens très utiles pour l'étude. Il est généreux sur les notes...
